						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Venkaṭēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>1236 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1159, Uttarāyaṇa-sankrānti, corresponding to 1236 A.D. December.</p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of 15 <hi rend="italic">chinnas</hi> (coins) for maintainig the <hi rend="italic">aradivvya</hi> probably for half day in the temple of Ishṭhakāmīśvaramahādēva at Gajjaramu by Polisēnaollasāni, the daughter of Ollupa Mallināyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
